data.text:
As the founder of Zubaida Foundation, Syed Murtuza is lovingly referred to by the community as Murtuza Uncle. He is actively involved in many of the Foundation's activities, especially events related to inter-faith and charity at Zubaida Foundation. He is the CEO of PDC Machines and an ameer at various other mosques in the area.

Naveed Malik, is among the founding community members involved in establishing Masjid Zubaida Foundation. He served as board member and then general secretary for the borad for several years before switching to volunteer role in necent years.

Naveed was born and raised in Pakistan where completed his education. He moved to Pennsylvania Levittown/Yardley area in 1999. He enjoys archery and bowhunting in his spare time.

He currently lives in Langhorne. Family members: Wife Shabana Malik, daughter Eman Naveed and son Azaan Naveed.

He can be contacted by phone at (267) 797-3043‬ ( leave voicemail ) or [email protected]
